<item>
            <title>[FLINK-2674] Rework windowing logic</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-2674</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The windowing logic needs a major overhaul. This follows the design documents: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/FLINK/Time+and+Order+in+Streams&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/FLINK/Time+and+Order+in+Streams&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=60624830&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=60624830&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Specifically, the following shortcomings need to be addressed:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Global parallel windows should be dropped&lt;br/&gt;
       -&amp;gt; for time, local windows are aligned and serve the same purpose&lt;br/&gt;
       -&amp;gt; there is currently no known robust and efficient parallel implementation of custom strategies &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Event time and out of order arrival needs to be supported&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Eviction of not accessed keys does not work. Non-accessed keys linger infinitely&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Performance is currently bad for time windows, due to a overly general implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Resources are leaking, threads are not shut down&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Elements are stored multiple times (discretizers, window buffers)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Finally, many implementations are buggy, produce wrong results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
